from keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator

train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255,width_shift_range=0.2,height_shift_range=0.2, horizontal_flip= True)
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)
eval_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)

train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    './train',
    target_size=(224,224),
    batch_size=15,
    class_mode='binary'
)

eval_generator = eval_datagen.flow_from_directory(
   './eval',
    target_size=(224,224),
    batch_size=15,
    class_mode='binary'
)

test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
   './test',
    target_size=(224,224),
    batch_size=15,
    class_mode='binary'
)

# vgg19_model = './vgg19_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels.h5'

model = models.Sequential()

vgg19_model = VGG19(
    include_top=True, weights='./vgg19_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels.h5',  input_shape=(224,224,3),
    classes=1000 #, classifier_activation='softmax'
    )
 
# Freeze all VGG layers
for layer in vgg19_model.layers[:]:
    layer.trainable = False
    
model.add(vgg19_model)
# model.add(layers.Flatten())
model.add(layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu'))
model.add(layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'))
model.add(layers.Dropout(0.1))
model.add(layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

model.summary()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

acc = history.history['acc']
val_acc = history.history['val_acc']
loss = history.history['loss']
val_loss = history.history['val_loss']

epochs = range(1,len(acc) +1)

plt.plot(epochs,acc,'bo',label='Training acc')
plt.plot(epochs,val_acc,'b',label='validation acc')
plt.title('train and validation acc')
plt.legend()

plt.figure()

plt.plot(epochs,loss,'bo',label='Training loss')
plt.plot(epochs,val_loss,'b',label='val_loss acc')
plt.title('train and validation loss')
plt.legend()

plt.show()
  1. The prediction accuracy of train set is always higher than the accuracy on validation set
  2. Compare with the model perfermence on Assignment 1, the predict accuracy is improved in the fisrt few epoch of training, but the final performence need further trainning.

# vgg19_model = './vgg19_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels.h5'

model = models.Sequential()

vgg19_model = VGG19(
    include_top=True, weights='./vgg19_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels.h5', input_tensor=None, input_shape=(224,224,3),
    pooling=None, classes=1000# , classifier_activation='softmax'
    )


# Freeze all VGG layers
for layer in vgg19_model.layers[3:]:
    layer.trainable = False
for layer in vgg19_model.layers[:2]:
    layer.trainable = True
    
model.add(vgg19_model)
# model.add(layers.Flatten())
model.add(layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu'))
model.add(layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'))
model.add(layers.Dropout(0.1))
model.add(layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])


model.summary()

from keras.preprocessing import image
from keras.applications.vgg19 import preprocess_input

def check_classes( val ):
    if val < 0.5:
        return "cat"
    if val > 0.5:
        return "dog"

# Load imgs from test directory
img_name = ['./test/cat/cat.2108.jpg', './test/cat/cat.2173.jpg', './test/cat/cat.373.jpg', 
            './test/cat/cat.3320.jpg', './test/cat/cat.518.jpg',
            './test/dog/dog.192.jpg', './test/dog/dog.326.jpg', './test/dog/dog.299.jpg',
            './test/dog/dog.1392.jpg','./test/dog/dog.2579.jpg']

plt.figure(figsize=(25,10))
for idx, img_n in enumerate(img_name):
    img = image.load_img(img_n, target_size=(224, 224)) 
    plt.subplot(2,5,idx+1)
    plt.imshow(img)

    x = image.img_to_array(img)
    x = np.expand_dims(x, axis=0)
    x = preprocess_input(x)

    predict_1 = model.predict(x)
    predict_2 = model_.predict(x)
    
    plt.title('Predict: [1] ' + check_classes(predict_1) + ' /  [2] ' + check_classes(predict_2))
    
print( "Model 1 acc: 100%   /  Model 2(fine-tunning) acc : 70%")

Model 1 acc: 100%   /  Model 2(fine-tunning) acc : 70%

From the result, we can conclude that the performence of fine tunning model is worse than the original one

With the pre-trained model, the performence of new model improved more stable. In my case, the final accuracy on validation set in assignmet1 are 0.78, 0.82, and 0.86 , 0.72 in this assignment. But for comparision of the final performence for each model, I think each model need to be further trainned with more epoch.
